cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper deals with the problem of overfitting in deep reinforcement learning and proposes a new benchmark environment for generalization in RL. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep convolutional architectures are used. The paper also discusses methods traditionally found in supervised learning, such as L2 regularization, dropout, data augmentation, and batch normalization, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
